36uint32_t GetDeviceVendorIdFromName(id<MTLDevice> metalDevice)
37{
38 struct Vendor
39 {
40 NSString *const trademark;
41 uint32_t vendorId;
42 };
43
44 constexpr Vendor kVendors[] = {{@"AMD", angle::kVendorID_AMD},
45 {@"Radeon", angle::kVendorID_AMD},
46 {@"Intel", angle::kVendorID_Intel},
47 {@"Geforce", angle::kVendorID_NVIDIA},
48 {@"Quadro", angle::kVendorID_NVIDIA}};
49 ANGLE_MTL_OBJC_SCOPE
50 {
51 if (metalDevice)
52 {
53 for (const Vendor &it : kVendors)
54 {
55 if ([metalDevice.name rangeOfString:it.trademark].location != NSNotFound)
56 {
57 return it.vendorId;
58 }
59 }
60 }
61
62 return 0;
63 }
64}

66#if TARGET_OS_OSX || TARGET_OS_MACCATALYST
67uint32_t GetDeviceVendorIdFromIOKit(id<MTLDevice> device)
68{
69 return angle::GetVendorIDFromMetalDeviceRegistryID(device.registryID);
70}
71#endif

73void GetSliceAndDepth(const ImageNativeIndex &index, GLint *layer, GLint *startDepth)
74{
75 *layer = *startDepth = 0;
76 if (!index.hasLayer())
77 {
78 return;
79 }
80
81 switch (index.getType())
82 {
83 case gl::TextureType::CubeMap:
84 *layer = index.cubeMapFaceIndex();
85 break;
86 case gl::TextureType::_2DArray:
87 *layer = index.getLayerIndex();
88 break;
89 case gl::TextureType::_3D:
90 *startDepth = index.getLayerIndex();
91 break;
92 default:
93 break;
94 }
95}
96GLint GetSliceOrDepth(const ImageNativeIndex &index)
97{
98 GLint layer, startDepth;
99 GetSliceAndDepth(index, &layer, &startDepth);
100
101 return std::max(layer, startDepth);
102}

106angle::Result InitializeTextureContents(const gl::Context *context,
107 const TextureRef &texture,
108 const Format &textureObjFormat,
109 const ImageNativeIndex &index)
110{
111 ASSERT(texture && texture->valid());
112 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
113
114 const angle::Format &actualAngleFormat = textureObjFormat.actualAngleFormat();
115 const gl::InternalFormat &intendedInternalFormat = textureObjFormat.intendedInternalFormat();
116
117 bool forceGPUInitialization = false;
118#if TARGET_OS_SIMULATOR
119 forceGPUInitialization = true;
120#endif // TARGET_OS_SIMULATOR
121
122 // This function is called in many places to initialize the content of a texture.
123 // So it's better we do the sanity check here instead of let the callers do it themselves:
124 if (!textureObjFormat.valid() || actualAngleFormat.isBlock || actualAngleFormat.depthBits > 0 ||
125 actualAngleFormat.stencilBits > 0)
126 {
127 // If dst format is compressed, ignore.
128 return angle::Result::Continue;
129 }
130
131 gl::Extents size = texture->size(index);
132
133 // Intialize the content to black
134 GLint layer = 0;
135 GLint startDepth = 0;
136 if (index.hasLayer())
137 {
138 switch (index.getType())
139 {
140 case gl::TextureType::CubeMap:
141 layer = index.cubeMapFaceIndex();
142 break;
143 case gl::TextureType::_2DArray:
144 layer = index.getLayerIndex();
145 break;
146 case gl::TextureType::_3D:
147 startDepth = index.getLayerIndex();
148 break;
149 default:
150 UNREACHABLE();
151 break;
152 }
153 }
154
155 if (texture->isCPUAccessible() && index.getType() != gl::TextureType::_2DMultisample &&
156 index.getType() != gl::TextureType::_2DMultisampleArray && !forceGPUInitialization)
157 {
158 const angle::Format &dstFormat = angle::Format::Get(textureObjFormat.actualFormatId);
159 const size_t dstRowPitch = dstFormat.pixelBytes * size.width;
160 angle::MemoryBuffer conversionRow;
161 ANGLE_CHECK_GL_ALLOC(contextMtl, conversionRow.resize(dstRowPitch));
162
163 if (textureObjFormat.initFunction)
164 {
165 textureObjFormat.initFunction(size.width, 1, 1, conversionRow.data(), dstRowPitch, 0);
166 }
167 else
168 {
169 if (!textureObjFormat.valid() || intendedInternalFormat.compressed ||
170 intendedInternalFormat.depthBits > 0 || intendedInternalFormat.stencilBits > 0)
171 {
172 // If source format is compressed, ignore.
173 return angle::Result::Continue;
174 }
175
176 const angle::Format &srcFormat = angle::Format::Get(
177 intendedInternalFormat.alphaBits > 0 ? angle::FormatID::R8G8B8A8_UNORM
178 : angle::FormatID::R8G8B8_UNORM);
179 const size_t srcRowPitch = srcFormat.pixelBytes * size.width;
180 angle::MemoryBuffer srcRow;
181 ANGLE_CHECK_GL_ALLOC(contextMtl, srcRow.resize(srcRowPitch));
182 memset(srcRow.data(), 0, srcRowPitch);
183
184 CopyImageCHROMIUM(srcRow.data(), srcRowPitch, srcFormat.pixelBytes, 0,
185 srcFormat.pixelReadFunction, conversionRow.data(), dstRowPitch,
186 dstFormat.pixelBytes, 0, dstFormat.pixelWriteFunction,
187 intendedInternalFormat.format, dstFormat.componentType, size.width, 1,
188 1, false, false, false);
189 }
190
191 auto mtlRowRegion = MTLRegionMake2D(0, 0, size.width, 1);
192
193 for (NSUInteger d = 0; d < static_cast<NSUInteger>(size.depth); ++d)
194 {
195 mtlRowRegion.origin.z = d + startDepth;
196 for (NSUInteger r = 0; r < static_cast<NSUInteger>(size.height); ++r)
197 {
198 mtlRowRegion.origin.y = r;
199
200 // Upload to texture
201 texture->replace2DRegion(contextMtl, mtlRowRegion, index.getNativeLevel(), layer,
202 conversionRow.data(), dstRowPitch);
203 }
204 }
205 } // if (texture->isCPUAccessible())
206 else
207 {
208 ANGLE_TRY(InitializeTextureContentsGPU(context, texture, textureObjFormat, index,
209 MTLColorWriteMaskAll));
210 }
211
212 return angle::Result::Continue;
213}
214
215angle::Result InitializeTextureContentsGPU(const gl::Context *context,
216 const TextureRef &texture,
217 const Format &textureObjFormat,
218 const ImageNativeIndex &index,
219 MTLColorWriteMask channelsToInit)
220{
221 // Only one slice can be initialized at a time.
222 ASSERT(!index.isLayered() || index.getType() == gl::TextureType::_3D);
223 if (index.isLayered() && index.getType() == gl::TextureType::_3D)
224 {
225 ImageNativeIndexIterator ite =
226 index.getLayerIterator(texture->depth(index.getNativeLevel()));
227 while (ite.hasNext())
228 {
229 ImageNativeIndex depthLayerIndex = ite.next();
230 ANGLE_TRY(InitializeTextureContentsGPU(context, texture, textureObjFormat,
231 depthLayerIndex, MTLColorWriteMaskAll));
232 }
233
234 return angle::Result::Continue;
235 }
236
237 if (textureObjFormat.hasDepthOrStencilBits())
238 {
239 // Depth stencil texture needs dedicated function.
240 return InitializeDepthStencilTextureContentsGPU(context, texture, textureObjFormat, index);
241 }
242
243 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
244 GLint sliceOrDepth = GetSliceOrDepth(index);
245
246 // Use clear render command
247 RenderTargetMtl tempRtt;
248 tempRtt.set(texture, index.getNativeLevel(), sliceOrDepth, textureObjFormat);
249
250 float clearAlpha = 0;
251 if (!textureObjFormat.intendedAngleFormat().alphaBits)
252 {
253 // if intended format doesn't have alpha, set it to 1.0.
254 clearAlpha = kEmulatedAlphaValue;
255 }
256
257 RenderCommandEncoder *encoder;
258 if (channelsToInit == MTLColorWriteMaskAll)
259 {
260 // If all channels will be initialized, use clear loadOp.
261 Optional<MTLClearColor> blackColor = MTLClearColorMake(0, 0, 0, clearAlpha);
262 encoder = contextMtl->getRenderTargetCommandEncoderWithClear(tempRtt, blackColor);
263 }
264 else
265 {
266 // temporarily enable color channels requested via channelsToInit. Some emulated format has
267 // some channels write mask disabled when the texture is created.
268 MTLColorWriteMask oldMask = texture->getColorWritableMask();
269 texture->setColorWritableMask(channelsToInit);
270
271 // If there are some channels don't need to be initialized, we must use clearWithDraw.
272 encoder = contextMtl->getRenderTargetCommandEncoder(tempRtt);
273
274 const angle::Format &angleFormat = textureObjFormat.actualAngleFormat();
275
276 ClearRectParams clearParams;
277 ClearColorValue clearColor;
278 if (angleFormat.isSint())
279 {
280 clearColor.setAsInt(0, 0, 0, (int)clearAlpha);
281 }
282 else if (angleFormat.isUint())
283 {
284 clearColor.setAsUInt(0, 0, 0, (int)clearAlpha);
285 }
286 else
287 {
288 clearColor.setAsFloat(0, 0, 0, clearAlpha);
289 }
290 clearParams.clearColor = clearColor;
291 clearParams.dstTextureSize = texture->sizeAt0();
292 clearParams.enabledBuffers.set(0);
293 clearParams.clearArea = gl::Rectangle(0, 0, texture->widthAt0(), texture->heightAt0());
294
295 ANGLE_TRY(
296 contextMtl->getDisplay()->getUtils().clearWithDraw(context, encoder, clearParams));
297
298 // Restore texture's intended write mask
299 texture->setColorWritableMask(oldMask);
300 }
301 encoder->setStoreAction(MTLStoreActionStore);
302
303 return angle::Result::Continue;
304}

306angle::Result InitializeDepthStencilTextureContentsGPU(const gl::Context *context,
307 const TextureRef &texture,
308 const Format &textureObjFormat,
309 const ImageNativeIndex &index)
310{
311 const MipmapNativeLevel &level = index.getNativeLevel();
312 // Use clear operation
313 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
314 const angle::Format &angleFormat = textureObjFormat.actualAngleFormat();
315 RenderTargetMtl rtMTL;
316
317 uint32_t layer = index.hasLayer() ? index.getLayerIndex() : 0;
318 rtMTL.set(texture, level, layer, textureObjFormat);
319 mtl::RenderPassDesc rpDesc;
320 // For formats such as MTLPixelFormatStencil8/GL_STENCIL_INDEX8 we only want to set the stencil attachment.
321 if (angleFormat.stencilBits && !angleFormat.depthBits)
322 {
323 rtMTL.toRenderPassAttachmentDesc(&rpDesc.stencilAttachment);
324 }
325 else
326 {
327 rtMTL.toRenderPassAttachmentDesc(&rpDesc.depthAttachment);
328 }
329 rpDesc.sampleCount = texture->samples();
330 if (angleFormat.depthBits)
331 {
332 rpDesc.depthAttachment.loadAction = MTLLoadActionClear;
333 rpDesc.depthAttachment.clearDepth = 1.0;
334 }
335 if (angleFormat.stencilBits)
336 {
337 rpDesc.stencilAttachment.loadAction = MTLLoadActionClear;
338 }
339
340 // End current render pass
341 contextMtl->endEncoding(true);
342
343 RenderCommandEncoder *encoder = contextMtl->getRenderPassCommandEncoder(rpDesc);
344 encoder->setStoreAction(MTLStoreActionStore);
345
346 return angle::Result::Continue;
347}

349angle::Result ReadTexturePerSliceBytes(const gl::Context *context,
350 const TextureRef &texture,
351 size_t bytesPerRow,
352 const gl::Rectangle &fromRegion,
353 const MipmapNativeLevel &mipLevel,
354 uint32_t sliceOrDepth,
355 uint8_t *dataOut)
356{
357 ASSERT(texture && texture->valid());
358 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
359 GLint layer = 0;
360 GLint startDepth = 0;
361 switch (texture->textureType())
362 {
363 case MTLTextureTypeCube:
364 case MTLTextureType2DArray:
365 layer = sliceOrDepth;
366 break;
367 case MTLTextureType3D:
368 startDepth = sliceOrDepth;
369 break;
370 default:
371 break;
372 }
373
374 MTLRegion mtlRegion = MTLRegionMake3D(fromRegion.x, fromRegion.y, startDepth, fromRegion.width,
375 fromRegion.height, 1);
376
377 texture->getBytes(contextMtl, bytesPerRow, 0, mtlRegion, mipLevel, layer, dataOut);
378
379 return angle::Result::Continue;
380}
381
382angle::Result ReadTexturePerSliceBytesToBuffer(const gl::Context *context,
383 const TextureRef &texture,
384 size_t bytesPerRow,
385 const gl::Rectangle &fromRegion,
386 const MipmapNativeLevel &mipLevel,
387 uint32_t sliceOrDepth,
388 uint32_t dstOffset,
389 const BufferRef &dstBuffer)
390{
391 ASSERT(texture && texture->valid());
392 ContextMtl *contextMtl = mtl::GetImpl(context);
393 GLint layer = 0;
394 GLint startDepth = 0;
395 switch (texture->textureType())
396 {
397 case MTLTextureTypeCube:
398 case MTLTextureType2DArray:
399 layer = sliceOrDepth;
400 break;
401 case MTLTextureType3D:
402 startDepth = sliceOrDepth;
403 break;
404 default:
405 break;
406 }
407
408 MTLRegion mtlRegion = MTLRegionMake3D(fromRegion.x, fromRegion.y, startDepth, fromRegion.width,
409 fromRegion.height, 1);
410
411 BlitCommandEncoder *blitEncoder = contextMtl->getBlitCommandEncoder();
412 blitEncoder->copyTextureToBuffer(texture, layer, mipLevel, mtlRegion.origin, mtlRegion.size,
413 dstBuffer, dstOffset, bytesPerRow, 0, MTLBlitOptionNone);
414
415 return angle::Result::Continue;
416}

418MTLViewport GetViewport(const gl::Rectangle &rect, double znear, double zfar)
419{
420 MTLViewport re;
421
422 re.originX = rect.x;
423 re.originY = rect.y;
424 re.width = rect.width;
425 re.height = rect.height;
426 re.znear = znear;
427 re.zfar = zfar;
428
429 return re;
430}
431
432MTLViewport GetViewportFlipY(const gl::Rectangle &rect,
433 NSUInteger screenHeight,
434 double znear,
435 double zfar)
436{
437 MTLViewport re;
438
439 re.originX = rect.x;
440 re.originY = static_cast<double>(screenHeight) - rect.y1();
441 re.width = rect.width;
442 re.height = rect.height;
443 re.znear = znear;
444 re.zfar = zfar;
445
446 return re;
447}
448
449MTLViewport GetViewport(const gl::Rectangle &rect,
450 NSUInteger screenHeight,
451 bool flipY,
452 double znear,
453 double zfar)
454{
455 if (flipY)
456 {
457 return GetViewportFlipY(rect, screenHeight, znear, zfar);
458 }
459
460 return GetViewport(rect, znear, zfar);
461}
462
463MTLScissorRect GetScissorRect(const gl::Rectangle &rect, NSUInteger screenHeight, bool flipY)
464{
465 MTLScissorRect re;
466
467 re.x = rect.x;
468 re.y = flipY ? (screenHeight - rect.y1()) : rect.y;
469 re.width = rect.width;
470 re.height = rect.height;
471
472 return re;
473}

475uint32_t GetDeviceVendorId(id<MTLDevice> metalDevice)
476{
477 uint32_t vendorId = 0;
478#if TARGET_OS_OSX || TARGET_OS_MACCATALYST
479 if (ANGLE_APPLE_AVAILABLE_XC(10.13, 13.0))
480 {
481 vendorId = GetDeviceVendorIdFromIOKit(metalDevice);
482 }
483#endif
484 if (!vendorId)
485 {
486 vendorId = GetDeviceVendorIdFromName(metalDevice);
487 }
488
489 return vendorId;
490}

492static MTLLanguageVersion GetUserSetOrHighestMSLVersion(const MTLLanguageVersion currentVersion)
493{
494 const std::string major_str = angle::GetEnvironmentVar(kANGLEMSLVersionMajorEnv);
495 const std::string minor_str = angle::GetEnvironmentVar(kANGLEMSLVersionMinorEnv);
496 if (major_str != "" && minor_str != "")
497 {
498 const int major = std::stoi(major_str);
499 const int minor = std::stoi(minor_str);
500#if !defined(NDEBUG)
501 NSLog(@"Forcing MSL Version: MTLLanguageVersion%d_%d\n", major, minor);
502#endif
503 switch (major)
504 {
505 case 1:
506 switch (minor)
507 {
508#if (defined(__IPHONE_9_0) && __IPHONE_OS_VERSION_MIN_REQUIRED >= __IPHONE_9_0) &&\
509 (TARGET_OS_IOS || TARGET_OS_TV) && !TARGET_OS_MACCATALYST
510 case 0: return MTLLanguageVersion1_0;
511#endif
512#if (defined(__MAC_10_11) && __MAC_OS_X_VERSION_MIN_REQUIRED >= __MAC_10_11) ||\
513 (defined(__IPHONE_9_0) && __IPHONE_OS_VERSION_MIN_REQUIRED >= __IPHONE_9_0) ||\
514 (defined(__TVOS_9_0) && __TV_OS_VERSION_MIN_REQUIRED >= __TVOS_9_0)
515 case 1: return MTLLanguageVersion1_1;
516#endif
517#if (defined(__MAC_10_12) && __MAC_OS_X_VERSION_MIN_REQUIRED >= __MAC_10_12) ||\
518 (defined(__IPHONE_10_0) && __IPHONE_OS_VERSION_MIN_REQUIRED >= __IPHONE_10_0) ||\
519 (defined(__TVOS_10_0) && __TV_OS_VERSION_MIN_REQUIRED >= __TVOS_10_0)
520 case 2: return MTLLanguageVersion1_2;
521#endif
522 default:
523 assert(0 && "Unsupported MSL Minor Language Version.");
524 }
525 break;
526 case 2:
527 switch (minor)
528 {
529#if (defined(__MAC_10_13) && __MAC_OS_X_VERSION_MIN_REQUIRED >= __MAC_10_13) ||\
530 (defined(__IPHONE_11_0) && __IPHONE_OS_VERSION_MIN_REQUIRED >= __IPHONE_11_0) ||\
531 (defined(__TVOS_11_0) && __TV_OS_VERSION_MIN_REQUIRED >= __TVOS_11_0)
532 case 0: return MTLLanguageVersion2_0;
533#endif
534#if (defined(__MAC_10_14) && __MAC_OS_X_VERSION_MIN_REQUIRED >= __MAC_10_14) ||\
535 (defined(__IPHONE_12_0) && __IPHONE_OS_VERSION_MIN_REQUIRED >= __IPHONE_12_0) ||\
536 (defined(__TVOS_12_0) && __TV_OS_VERSION_MIN_REQUIRED >= __TVOS_12_0)
537 case 1: return MTLLanguageVersion2_1;
538#endif
539#if (defined(__MAC_10_15) && __MAC_OS_X_VERSION_MIN_REQUIRED >= __MAC_10_15) ||\
540 (defined(__IPHONE_13_0) && __IPHONE_OS_VERSION_MIN_REQUIRED >= __IPHONE_13_0) ||\
541 (defined(__TVOS_13_0) && __TV_OS_VERSION_MIN_REQUIRED >= __TVOS_13_0)
542 case 2: return MTLLanguageVersion2_2;
543#endif
544#if (defined(__MAC_11_0) && __MAC_OS_X_VERSION_MIN_REQUIRED >= __MAC_11_0) ||\
545 (defined(__IPHONE_14_0) && __IPHONE_OS_VERSION_MIN_REQUIRED >= __IPHONE_14_0) ||\
546 (defined(__TVOS_14_0) && __TV_OS_VERSION_MIN_REQUIRED >= __TVOS_14_0)
547 case 3: return MTLLanguageVersion2_3;
548#endif
549 default:
550 assert(0 && "Unsupported MSL Minor Language Version.");
551 }
552 break;
553 default:
554 assert(0 && "Unsupported MSL Major Language Version.");
555 }
556 }
557 return currentVersion;
558}

560AutoObjCPtr<id<MTLLibrary>> CreateShaderLibrary(id<MTLDevice> metalDevice,
561 const std::string &source,
562 NSDictionary<NSString *, NSObject *> * substitutionMacros,
563 AutoObjCPtr<NSError *> *error)
564{
565 return CreateShaderLibrary(metalDevice, source.c_str(), source.size(), substitutionMacros, error);
566}
567
568AutoObjCPtr<id<MTLLibrary>> CreateShaderLibrary(id<MTLDevice> metalDevice,
569 const std::string &source,
570 AutoObjCPtr<NSError *> *error)
571{
572 return CreateShaderLibrary(metalDevice, source.c_str(), source.size(),@{}, error);
573}
574
575AutoObjCPtr<id<MTLLibrary>> CreateShaderLibrary(id<MTLDevice> metalDevice,
576 const char *source,
577 size_t sourceLen,
578 NSDictionary<NSString *, NSObject *> * substitutionMacros,
579 AutoObjCPtr<NSError *> *errorOut)
580{
581 ANGLE_MTL_OBJC_SCOPE
582 {
583 NSError *nsError = nil;
584 auto nsSource = [[NSString alloc] initWithBytesNoCopy:const_cast<char *>(source)
585 length:sourceLen
586 encoding:NSUTF8StringEncoding
587 freeWhenDone:NO];
588 auto options = [[[MTLCompileOptions alloc] init] ANGLE_MTL_AUTORELEASE];
589 // Mark all positions in VS with attribute invariant as non-optimizable
590#if (defined(__MAC_11_0) && __MAC_OS_X_VERSION_MIN_REQUIRED >= __MAC_11_0) ||\
591 (defined(__IPHONE_14_0) && __IPHONE_OS_VERSION_MIN_REQUIRED >= __IPHONE_14_0) ||\
592 (defined(__TVOS_14_0) && __TV_OS_VERSION_MIN_REQUIRED >= __TVOS_14_0)
593 options.preserveInvariance = true;
594#else
595 // No preserveInvariance available compiling from source, so just disable fastmath.
596 options.fastMathEnabled = false;
597#endif
598 options.languageVersion = GetUserSetOrHighestMSLVersion(options.languageVersion);
599 options.preprocessorMacros = substitutionMacros;
600 auto library = [metalDevice newLibraryWithSource:nsSource options:options error:&nsError];
601 if (angle::GetEnvironmentVar(kANGLEPrintMSLEnv)[0] == '1')
602 {
603 NSLog(@"%@\n", nsSource);
604 }
605 [nsSource ANGLE_MTL_AUTORELEASE];
606
607 *errorOut = std::move(nsError);
608
609 return [library ANGLE_MTL_AUTORELEASE];
610 }
611}
612
613AutoObjCPtr<id<MTLLibrary>> CreateShaderLibraryFromBinary(id<MTLDevice> metalDevice,
614 const uint8_t *binarySource,
615 size_t binarySourceLen,
616 AutoObjCPtr<NSError *> *errorOut)
617{
618 ANGLE_MTL_OBJC_SCOPE
619 {
620 NSError *nsError = nil;
621 auto shaderSourceData =
622 dispatch_data_create(binarySource, binarySourceLen, dispatch_get_main_queue(),
623 ^{
624 });
625
626 auto library = [metalDevice newLibraryWithData:shaderSourceData error:&nsError];
627
628 [shaderSourceData ANGLE_MTL_AUTORELEASE];
629
630 *errorOut = std::move(nsError);
631
632 return [library ANGLE_MTL_AUTORELEASE];
633 }
634}

636MTLTextureType GetTextureType(gl::TextureType glType)
637{
638 switch (glType)
639 {
640 case gl::TextureType::_2D:
641 return MTLTextureType2D;
642 case gl::TextureType::CubeMap:
643 return MTLTextureTypeCube;
644 default:
645 return MTLTextureTypeInvalid;
646 }
647}

649MTLSamplerMinMagFilter GetFilter(GLenum filter)
650{
651 switch (filter)
652 {
653 case GL_LINEAR_MIPMAP_LINEAR:
654 case GL_LINEAR_MIPMAP_NEAREST:
655 case GL_LINEAR:
656 return MTLSamplerMinMagFilterLinear;
657 case GL_NEAREST_MIPMAP_LINEAR:
658 case GL_NEAREST_MIPMAP_NEAREST:
659 case GL_NEAREST:
660 return MTLSamplerMinMagFilterNearest;
661 default:
662 UNIMPLEMENTED();
663 return MTLSamplerMinMagFilterNearest;
664 }
665}
666
667MTLSamplerMipFilter GetMipmapFilter(GLenum filter)
668{
669 switch (filter)
670 {
671 case GL_LINEAR:
672 case GL_NEAREST:
673 return MTLSamplerMipFilterNotMipmapped;
674 case GL_LINEAR_MIPMAP_LINEAR:
675 case GL_NEAREST_MIPMAP_LINEAR:
676 return MTLSamplerMipFilterLinear;
677 case GL_NEAREST_MIPMAP_NEAREST:
678 case GL_LINEAR_MIPMAP_NEAREST:
679 return MTLSamplerMipFilterNearest;
680 default:
681 UNIMPLEMENTED();
682 return MTLSamplerMipFilterNotMipmapped;
683 }
684}
685
686MTLSamplerAddressMode GetSamplerAddressMode(GLenum wrap)
687{
688 switch (wrap)
689 {
690 case GL_REPEAT:
691 return MTLSamplerAddressModeRepeat;
692 case GL_MIRRORED_REPEAT:
693 return MTLSamplerAddressModeMirrorRepeat;
694 case GL_CLAMP_TO_BORDER:
695 // ES doesn't have border support
696 return MTLSamplerAddressModeClampToEdge;

906MTLColorWriteMask GetEmulatedColorWriteMask(const mtl::Format &mtlFormat, bool *emulatedChannelsOut)
907{
908 const angle::Format &intendedFormat = mtlFormat.intendedAngleFormat();
909 const angle::Format &actualFormat = mtlFormat.actualAngleFormat();
910 bool emulatedChannels = false;
911 MTLColorWriteMask colorWritableMask = MTLColorWriteMaskAll;
912 if (intendedFormat.alphaBits == 0 && actualFormat.alphaBits)
913 {
914 emulatedChannels = true;
915 // Disable alpha write to this texture
916 colorWritableMask = colorWritableMask & (~MTLColorWriteMaskAlpha);
917 }
918 if (intendedFormat.luminanceBits == 0)
919 {
920 if (intendedFormat.redBits == 0 && actualFormat.redBits)
921 {
922 emulatedChannels = true;
923 // Disable red write to this texture
924 colorWritableMask = colorWritableMask & (~MTLColorWriteMaskRed);
925 }
926 if (intendedFormat.greenBits == 0 && actualFormat.greenBits)
927 {
928 emulatedChannels = true;
929 // Disable green write to this texture
930 colorWritableMask = colorWritableMask & (~MTLColorWriteMaskGreen);
931 }
932 if (intendedFormat.blueBits == 0 && actualFormat.blueBits)
933 {
934 emulatedChannels = true;
935 // Disable blue write to this texture
936 colorWritableMask = colorWritableMask & (~MTLColorWriteMaskBlue);
937 }
938 }
939
940 *emulatedChannelsOut = emulatedChannels;
941
942 return colorWritableMask;
943}
944
945MTLColorWriteMask GetEmulatedColorWriteMask(const mtl::Format &mtlFormat)
946{
947 // Ignore emulatedChannels boolean value
948 bool emulatedChannels;
949 return GetEmulatedColorWriteMask(mtlFormat, &emulatedChannels);
950}
951
952bool IsFormatEmulated(const mtl::Format &mtlFormat)
953{
954 bool emulatedChannels;
955 (void)GetEmulatedColorWriteMask(mtlFormat, &emulatedChannels);
956 return emulatedChannels;
957}

971NSUInteger GetMaxRenderTargetSizeForDeviceInBytes(id<MTLDevice> device)

1004bool SupportsIOSGPUFamily(id<MTLDevice> device, uint8_t iOSFamily)
1005{
1006#if (!TARGET_OS_IOS && !TARGET_OS_TV) || TARGET_OS_MACCATALYST
1007 return false;
1008#else
1009# if (__IPHONE_OS_VERSION_MAX_ALLOWED >= 130000) || (__TV_OS_VERSION_MAX_ALLOWED >= 130000)
1010 // If device supports [MTLDevice supportsFamily:], then use it.
1011 if (ANGLE_APPLE_AVAILABLE_I(13.0))
1012 {
1013 MTLGPUFamily family;
1014 switch (iOSFamily)
1015 {
1016 case 1:
1017 family = MTLGPUFamilyApple1;
1018 break;
1019 case 2:
1020 family = MTLGPUFamilyApple2;
1021 break;
1022 case 3:
1023 family = MTLGPUFamilyApple3;
1024 break;
1025 case 4:
1026 family = MTLGPUFamilyApple4;
1027 break;
1028 case 5:
1029 family = MTLGPUFamilyApple5;
1030 break;
1031# if TARGET_OS_IOS
1032 case 6:
1033 family = MTLGPUFamilyApple6;
1034 break;
1035# endif
1036 default:
1037 return false;
1038 }
1039 return [device supportsFamily:family];
1040 } // Metal 2.2
1041# endif // __IPHONE_OS_VERSION_MAX_ALLOWED
1042
1043 // If device doesn't support [MTLDevice supportsFamily:], then use
1044 // [MTLDevice supportsFeatureSet:].
1045 MTLFeatureSet featureSet;
1046 switch (iOSFamily)
1047 {
1048# if TARGET_OS_IOS
1049 case 1:
1050 featureSet = MTLFeatureSet_iOS_GPUFamily1_v1;
1051 break;
1052 case 2:
1053 featureSet = MTLFeatureSet_iOS_GPUFamily2_v1;
1054 break;
1055 case 3:
1056 featureSet = MTLFeatureSet_iOS_GPUFamily3_v1;
1057 break;
1058 case 4:
1059 featureSet = MTLFeatureSet_iOS_GPUFamily4_v1;
1060 break;
1061# if __IPHONE_OS_VERSION_MAX_ALLOWED >= 120000
1062 case 5:
1063 featureSet = MTLFeatureSet_iOS_GPUFamily5_v1;
1064 break;
1065# endif // __IPHONE_OS_VERSION_MAX_ALLOWED
1066# elif TARGET_OS_TV
1067 case 1:
1068 case 2:
1069 featureSet = MTLFeatureSet_tvOS_GPUFamily1_v1;
1070 break;
1071# endif // TARGET_OS_IOS
1072 default:
1073 return false;
1074 }
1075
1076 return [device supportsFeatureSet:featureSet];
1077#endif // TARGET_OS_IOS || TARGET_OS_TV
1078}
1079
1080bool SupportsMacGPUFamily(id<MTLDevice> device, uint8_t macFamily)
1081{
1082#if TARGET_OS_OSX || TARGET_OS_MACCATALYST
1083# if defined(__MAC_10_15)
1084 // If device supports [MTLDevice supportsFamily:], then use it.
1085 if (ANGLE_APPLE_AVAILABLE_XC(10.15, 13.0))
1086 {
1087 MTLGPUFamily family;
1088
1089 switch (macFamily)
1090 {
1091# if TARGET_OS_MACCATALYST
1092 case 1:
1093 family = MTLGPUFamilyMacCatalyst1;
1094 break;
1095 case 2:
1096 family = MTLGPUFamilyMacCatalyst2;
1097 break;
1098# else // TARGET_OS_MACCATALYST
1099 case 1:
1100 family = MTLGPUFamilyMac1;
1101 break;
1102 case 2:
1103 family = MTLGPUFamilyMac2;
1104 break;
1105# endif // TARGET_OS_MACCATALYST
1106 default:
1107 return false;
1108 }
1109
1110 return [device supportsFamily:family];
1111 } // Metal 2.2
1112# endif
1113
1114 // If device doesn't support [MTLDevice supportsFamily:], then use
1115 // [MTLDevice supportsFeatureSet:].
1116# if TARGET_OS_MACCATALYST
1117 UNREACHABLE();
1118 return false;
1119# else
1120 MTLFeatureSet featureSet;
1121 switch (macFamily)
1122 {
1123 case 1:
1124 featureSet = MTLFeatureSet_macOS_GPUFamily1_v1;
1125 break;
1126# if defined(__MAC_10_14)
1127 case 2:
1128 featureSet = MTLFeatureSet_macOS_GPUFamily2_v1;
1129 break;
1130# endif
1131 default:
1132 return false;
1133 }
1134 return [device supportsFeatureSet:featureSet];
1135# endif // TARGET_OS_MACCATALYST
1136#else // #if TARGET_OS_OSX || TARGET_OS_MACCATALYST
1137
1138 return false;
1139
1140#endif
1141}
1142
1143static NSUInteger getNextLocationForFormat(const FormatCaps &caps,
1144 bool isMSAA,
1145 NSUInteger currentRenderTargetSize)
1146{
1147 assert(!caps.compressed);
1148 uint8_t alignment = caps.alignment;
1149 NSUInteger pixelBytes = caps.pixelBytes;
1150 NSUInteger pixelBytesMSAA = caps.pixelBytesMSAA;
1151 pixelBytes = isMSAA ? pixelBytesMSAA : pixelBytes;
1152
1153 currentRenderTargetSize = (currentRenderTargetSize + (alignment - 1)) & ~(alignment - 1);
1154 currentRenderTargetSize += pixelBytes;
1155 return currentRenderTargetSize;
1156}
1157
1158NSUInteger ComputeTotalSizeUsedForMTLRenderPassDescriptor(const MTLRenderPassDescriptor *descriptor,
1159 const Context *context,
1160 id<MTLDevice> device)
1161{
1162 NSUInteger currentRenderTargetSize = 0;
1163
1164 for (NSUInteger i = 0; i < GetMaxNumberOfRenderTargetsForDevice(device); i++)
1165 {
1166 MTLPixelFormat pixelFormat = descriptor.colorAttachments[i].texture.pixelFormat;
1167 bool isMsaa = descriptor.colorAttachments[i].texture.sampleCount > 1;
1168 if (pixelFormat != MTLPixelFormatInvalid)
1169 {
1170 const FormatCaps &caps = context->getDisplay()->getNativeFormatCaps(pixelFormat);
1171 currentRenderTargetSize =
1172 getNextLocationForFormat(caps, isMsaa, currentRenderTargetSize);
1173 }
1174 }
1175 if (descriptor.depthAttachment.texture.pixelFormat ==
1176 descriptor.stencilAttachment.texture.pixelFormat)
1177 {
1178 bool isMsaa = descriptor.depthAttachment.texture.sampleCount > 1;
1179 if (descriptor.depthAttachment.texture.pixelFormat != MTLPixelFormatInvalid)
1180 {
1181 const FormatCaps &caps = context->getDisplay()->getNativeFormatCaps(
1182 descriptor.depthAttachment.texture.pixelFormat);
1183 currentRenderTargetSize =
1184 getNextLocationForFormat(caps, isMsaa, currentRenderTargetSize);
1185 }
1186 }
1187 else
1188 {
1189 if (descriptor.depthAttachment.texture.pixelFormat != MTLPixelFormatInvalid)
1190 {
1191 bool isMsaa = descriptor.depthAttachment.texture.sampleCount > 1;
1192 const FormatCaps &caps = context->getDisplay()->getNativeFormatCaps(
1193 descriptor.depthAttachment.texture.pixelFormat);
1194 currentRenderTargetSize =
1195 getNextLocationForFormat(caps, isMsaa, currentRenderTargetSize);
1196 }
1197 if (descriptor.stencilAttachment.texture.pixelFormat != MTLPixelFormatInvalid)
1198 {
1199 bool isMsaa = descriptor.stencilAttachment.texture.sampleCount > 1;
1200 const FormatCaps &caps = context->getDisplay()->getNativeFormatCaps(
1201 descriptor.stencilAttachment.texture.pixelFormat);
1202 currentRenderTargetSize =
1203 getNextLocationForFormat(caps, isMsaa, currentRenderTargetSize);
1204 }
1205 }
1206 return currentRenderTargetSize;
1207}
1208NSUInteger ComputeTotalSizeUsedForMTLRenderPipelineDescriptor(
1209 const MTLRenderPipelineDescriptor *descriptor,
1210 const Context *context,
1211 id<MTLDevice> device)
1212{
1213 NSUInteger currentRenderTargetSize = 0;
1214 bool isMsaa = descriptor.sampleCount > 1;
1215 for (NSUInteger i = 0; i < GetMaxNumberOfRenderTargetsForDevice(device); i++)
1216 {
1217 MTLRenderPipelineColorAttachmentDescriptor *color = descriptor.colorAttachments[i];
1218 if (color.pixelFormat != MTLPixelFormatInvalid)
1219 {
1220 const FormatCaps &caps = context->getDisplay()->getNativeFormatCaps(color.pixelFormat);
1221 currentRenderTargetSize =
1222 getNextLocationForFormat(caps, isMsaa, currentRenderTargetSize);
1223 }
1224 }
1225 if (descriptor.depthAttachmentPixelFormat == descriptor.stencilAttachmentPixelFormat)
1226 {
1227 if (descriptor.depthAttachmentPixelFormat != MTLPixelFormatInvalid)
1228 {
1229 const FormatCaps &caps =
1230 context->getDisplay()->getNativeFormatCaps(descriptor.depthAttachmentPixelFormat);
1231 currentRenderTargetSize =
1232 getNextLocationForFormat(caps, isMsaa, currentRenderTargetSize);
1233 }
1234 }
1235 else
1236 {
1237 if (descriptor.depthAttachmentPixelFormat != MTLPixelFormatInvalid)
1238 {
1239 const FormatCaps &caps =
1240 context->getDisplay()->getNativeFormatCaps(descriptor.depthAttachmentPixelFormat);
1241 currentRenderTargetSize =
1242 getNextLocationForFormat(caps, isMsaa, currentRenderTargetSize);
1243 }
1244 if (descriptor.stencilAttachmentPixelFormat != MTLPixelFormatInvalid)
1245 {
1246 const FormatCaps &caps =
1247 context->getDisplay()->getNativeFormatCaps(descriptor.stencilAttachmentPixelFormat);
1248 currentRenderTargetSize =
1249 getNextLocationForFormat(caps, isMsaa, currentRenderTargetSize);
1250 }
1251 }
1252 return currentRenderTargetSize;
1253}

1273angle::Result TriangleFanBoundCheck(ContextMtl *context, size_t numTris)
1274{
1275 bool indexCheck =
1276 (numTris > std::numeric_limits<unsigned int>::max() / (sizeof(unsigned int) * 3));
1277 ANGLE_CHECK(context, !indexCheck,
1278 "Failed to create a scratch index buffer for GL_TRIANGLE_FAN, "
1279 "too many indices required.",
1280 GL_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
1281 return angle::Result::Continue;
1282}
1283
1284angle::Result GetTriangleFanIndicesCount(ContextMtl *context,
1285 GLsizei vetexCount,
1286 uint32_t *numElemsOut)
1287{
1288 size_t numTris = vetexCount - 2;
1289 ANGLE_TRY(TriangleFanBoundCheck(context, numTris));
1290 size_t numIndices = numTris * 3;
1291 ANGLE_CHECK(context, numIndices <= std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max(),
1292 "Failed to create a scratch index buffer for GL_TRIANGLE_FAN, "
1293 "too many indices required.",
1294 GL_OUT_OF_MEMORY);
1295
1296 *numElemsOut = static_cast<uint32_t>(numIndices);
1297 return angle::Result::Continue;
1298}

1300angle::Result CreateMslShader(mtl::Context *context,
1301 id<MTLLibrary> shaderLib,
1302 NSString * shaderName,
1303 MTLFunctionConstantValues *funcConstants,
1304 id<MTLFunction> *shaderOut)
1305{
1306 NSError *nsErr = nil;
1307
1308 id<MTLFunction> mtlShader;
1309 if (funcConstants)
1310 {
1311 mtlShader = [shaderLib newFunctionWithName:shaderName
1312 constantValues:funcConstants
1313 error:&nsErr];
1314 }
1315 else
1316 {
1317 mtlShader = [shaderLib newFunctionWithName:shaderName];
1318 }
1319
1320 [mtlShader ANGLE_MTL_AUTORELEASE];
1321 if (nsErr && !mtlShader)
1322 {
1323 std::ostringstream ss;
1324 ss << "Internal error compiling Metal shader:\n"
1325 << nsErr.localizedDescription.UTF8String << "\n";
1326
1327 ERR() << ss.str();
1328
1329 ANGLE_MTL_CHECK(context, false, GL_INVALID_OPERATION);
1330 }
1331 *shaderOut = mtlShader;
1332 return angle::Result::Continue;
1333}
1334
1335angle::Result CreateMslShader(Context *context,
1336 id<MTLLibrary> shaderLib,
1337 NSString * shaderName,
1338 MTLFunctionConstantValues *funcConstants,
1339 AutoObjCPtr<id<MTLFunction>> *shaderOut)
1340{
1341 id<MTLFunction> outFunction;
1342 ANGLE_TRY(CreateMslShader(context, shaderLib, shaderName, funcConstants, &outFunction));
1343 shaderOut->retainAssign(outFunction);
1344 return angle::Result::Continue;
1345
1346}
